OL,4,CRacism blamed for failure to
OL,5,Ccommemorate black and Asian troops
OL,6, Tens of thousands of predominantly
OL,7, black and Asian service personnel who
OL,8, died fighting for the British Empire
OL,9, were not properly commemorated due to
OL,10, "pervasive racism", a report has said.
OL,12,FSome troops were commemorated
OL,13,Fcollectively or their names were
OL,14,Frecorded in registers, while their
OL,15,Fwhite counterparts had headstones.
OL,17,FThe Commonwealth War Graves Commission
OL,18,Fhas apologised over its findings.
OL,20,FLabour MP David Lammy called it a
OL,21,F"watershed moment".
